60 Warrior<br>
Mith Marr<br>
(Imperial Guardians)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukaladornus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kaladornus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/8/02 10:31:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4090.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sunderfury</span><hr size=1> Remember the haste @ 100% would only be 25/18. So 36% of this = 29.52 so your weap is a 25/29.52 (round however you want, prolly UP <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
It's not bad, and really not bad for a free drop, but you can get higher ratio 2hs for free as well, like in maidens end.<br>
<br>
At the end of the day, the dependence on just using one weapon will not outweigh the benefit you would get from the 5k or so you get from selling your SCHW. SS gaunt MQ is probably the best thing I could think of in that slot for the money, and it wont be a life changing hp upgrade for you anyway. <br>
<br>
Item haste is Item haste and you cannot stack this with anything besides Spell or Song haste.<br>
<br>
Just one Lizard's opinion.<br>
<br>
Jakle<br>
